{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*13>}13{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The word “blessed” is similar in concept to the words: “merciful” or “gracious” when 
applied to God. Just as merciful means that He is merciful, the source of mercy, so too, blessed 
means that He is the source of blessing.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Avudraham{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*14>}14{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Generally speaking, the name Adonoy is understood as it is pronouncedÐAdonoyÐ, my 
Master, and indicates His rule and providence of the universe. When reciting the {\highlight7 <IT>}Shema{\highlight7 <ITC>} however, 
one should bear in mind the {\highlight7 <IT>}written{\highlight7 <ITC>} character of the Name which indicates God’s everpresent 
existence. He wasÐisÐand ever will be.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Vilna Gaon{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*15>}15{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}This may mean either that man was formed by God’s wisdom, or that God formed man 
and endowed him with wisdom.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*16>}16{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}In refutation of those who claim that God is not concerned with earthly matters, we 
declare that even in the presence of His {\highlight7 <IT>}glorious throne,{\highlight7 <ITC>} where He is surrounded by myriads of 
angels, He is aware of the mundane needs of each individual.Ð{\highlight7 <IT>}Vilna Gaon{\highlight7 <ITC>}{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*17>}17{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}This statement refers to the time when the dead will be resurrected.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*18>}18{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}Thus it is said, “I will praise Adonoy with my life, I will sing to my God with my being” 
({\highlight7 <IT>}Psalms{\highlight7 <ITC>} 146:2).{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*19>}19{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}This is a reference to God’s restoring of the soul each morning following its departure 
while the person sleeps.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
{\highlight7 @b1}{\highlight7 <EM>}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ6>}{\highlight7 <SUP2.5>}{\highlight7 <*20>}20{\highlight7 @b2}{\highlight7 <EN>}{\highlight7 <SZ9>}{\highlight7 <SUP0>}The observance and fulfillment of His commandments makes a person holy.{\highlight7 <QL>}\par
